<task id="testing-remote-wsdl-files">
  <title>Testing Remote WSDL Files</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>WSDL documents<indexterm>SOAP analyzer<indexterm>Test remote
            files</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>WSDL SOAP Analyzer tool<indexterm>Test remote files</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p>To open and test a remote WSDL file the steps are the following:</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Go to <menucascade product="editor developer">
            <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol><image href="../img/WsdlShowDialog16.png" id="image_mnh_zxh_5r"/>WSDL SOAP
              Analyzer</uicontrol>
          </menucascade>
          <menucascade product="editorEclipse developerEclipse">
            <uicontrol>Window</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Show View</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Other</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol keyref="product"/>
            <uicontrol><image href="../img/WsdlShowDialog16.png" id="image_uph_jyn_ds"/>WSDL SOAP
              Analyzer</uicontrol>
          </menucascade>.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd><ph product="editor developer">On the <uicontrol>WSDL File</uicontrol> tab</ph>
          <ph product="editorEclipse developerEclipse">Click the <uicontrol>Choose WSDL</uicontrol> button and</ph>
          enter the URL of the remote WSDL file.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol> button.</cmd>
        <stepresult>This will open the <xref
            href="composing-web-service-calls.dita#composing-web-service-calls"
              ><uicontrol>WSDL SOAP Analyzer</uicontrol> tool</xref>. In the <uicontrol>Saved SOAP
            Request</uicontrol> tab you can open directly a previously saved Web Service SOAP Call
          (WSSC) file, thus skipping the analysis phase.</stepresult>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>